# Excludes from the docker build context for the local-dev compose stack.
# Compose services use `build.context: .` (repo root) so they can COPY
# both LookseeCore and their own service tree. Everything below is either
# unrelated to those builds or rebuilt inside the container anyway.

# ---- VCS, IDE, OS ----
.git
.github
.idea
.kiro
.claude
**/*.iml
**/.project
**/.classpath
**/.settings
**/.DS_Store
**/Thumbs.db

# ---- Local .env / secrets ----
.env
.env.*
!.env.example
!.env.local.example
**/*.pem
**/*credentials*.json

# ---- Java / Maven build artifacts (rebuilt inside the container) ----
**/target
**/.mvn
**/.m2

# ---- Node / Angular build artifacts ----
**/node_modules
**/dist
**/.npm
**/.next
**/coverage
**/npm-debug.log*
**/yarn-error.log*

# ---- Top-level directories that no local-stack image needs ----
# Browser extensions, VS Code plugin, IaC, docs, and the QA testbed
# are not built into any compose image. Excluding them keeps the build
# context small.
LookseeChromeExtension
look-see-VSCode-plugin
browser-service
LookseeIaC
docs
qa-testbed
tests
page-audit-enrichment
LEGACY_REMOTES.txt
README.md
*.md
!README-LOCAL.md

# ---- Terraform state, if any ----
**/.terraform
**/*.tfstate
**/*.tfstate.*
